  "texts": [
    "Resources propagating these CTs, or to be more precise, all of the CTs, are often unreliable due to their lack of transparency, questionable methodologies, diverse origins, and tendency to propagate misinformation or 'fake news' without rigorous fact-checking or accountability, and that is how most of the CTs start spreading all over the Internet.",
    "Next, we analyze the most frequent CTs in the original dataset.To determine which CTs are discussed the most, we did a frequency analysis by going through the dataset and seeing how many times each CT is mentioned.",
    "It can give us which CTs are the most prevalent.",
    "As shown in Fig. 13, the frequency of QAnon CTs increased after the emergence of COVID-19 in late 2020, which was one year after the initial appearance of COVID-19.",
    "According to Morelock et al. [82], there is a connection between QAnon and COVID-19 CTs, as people are finding it difficult to trust the information they receive and are becoming less interested in learning from experts."
  ]
}